{"key":"post-9909753","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9909753</id>\n<content>You don't inoculate manure or other bulk substrates with spores.&amp;nbsp; You inoculate grains or brf cakes, and when those are fully colonized, you use them as spawn to inoculate the manure.&amp;nbsp; That's where you went wrong.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Next time, when your grains or brf cakes are colonized, inoculate pasteurized manure in a shallow tray with your copelandia spawn.&amp;nbsp; Make the total substrate no thicker than 1 1/2&quot;, and then when it's colonized, put a 1/4&quot; peat/verm casing layer on top.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9909898</next>\n<prev>9909752</prev>\n<first>9909690</first>\n<last>9909898</last>\n<when>1236191108</when>\n<utime>03/04/09 08:25 PM</utime>\n</post>"}